  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Project to strengthen the resilience of households rural town of Koumbri</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Koubri is in the Northern Region of Burkina and has endured especially dry seasons and fewer days of rainfall due to climate change. The community has also been affected by shallow soils and low capacity investment, hindering their ability to cover their basic needs. This project aims to strengthen the resilience of union members, gravely affected by the effects of climate change. This building resilience will be achieved through two specific objectives:
- Adapting agricultural production systems to climate change;
- Improving organizational and functional capabilities UGNK to render quality services to its members to reduce the effects of climate change on their household.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The activities associated with this project include:

- reinforcement of the technical capacity of producers for the production of basic speculations : sorghum , millet, maize and cowpea , and groundnut
-developing and conducting Farmers Field Schools by endogenous animators 
-training endogenous animators on the techniques of animal production (sheep and goat fattening ) and basic veterinary care
-Establishing and leading the demonstration of herds
-training endogenous animators on forage production techniques and hay / forage conservation</narrative>
  </description>
